    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Slice your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>aubergine wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and put in the oven for an initial 10 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-tamarind-curry-w-rice-onion-bhajis-and-chutney/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot (with a matching lid) over a high heat with a little <strong>butter, </strong>then once melted, add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>black mustard seeds </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>golden rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-tamarind-curry-w-rice-onion-bhajis-and-chutney/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel<strong> </strong>and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-tamarind-curry-w-rice-onion-bhajis-and-chutney/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine has had 10 min, add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to the tray[s]</p><p>Add your <strong>onion bhajis </strong>to another tray (or two!)</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 10-15 min or until the aubergine is tender and slightly charred, the tomatoes are blistered and the bhajis<strong> </strong>are warmed through</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-tamarind-curry-w-rice-onion-bhajis-and-chutney/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining black</strong> <strong>mustard seeds </strong>and cook for 1 min or until they start to pop</p><p>Then, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly browned</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-tamarind-curry-w-rice-onion-bhajis-and-chutney/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock </strong>in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [510ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Once browned, add the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until softened, then once softened, add your <strong>curry powder </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>coconut stock </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and stir it all together, bring to the boil over a high heat then reduce the heat to medium and cook for a further 5-7 min or until the sauce has reduced slightly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-tamarind-curry-w-rice-onion-bhajis-and-chutney/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, pick the <strong>coriander</strong> from their stems, discard the stems</p><p>Once the sauce has reduced, add the <strong>roasted aubergine </strong>and <strong>blistered tomatoes </strong>to the pan with your <strong>tamarind paste </strong>and <strong>garam masala</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and stir it all together, cook for 1-2 min further or until warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>aubergine, tamarind & tomato curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-tamarind-curry-w-rice-onion-bhajis-and-chutney/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>aubergine, tamarind & tomato curry </strong>with the <strong>golden rice</strong>, <strong>bhajis</strong> and <strong>mint & coriander chutney </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
